Guidelime.registerGuide(
[[
[N42-43 Stranglethorn Vale]
[GA Horde]
[D A guide created by T H A C E N#9446\Based on Joana's Speed Leveling guide https://www.joanasworld.com]
01) Once you land, next to you from Fleet Master Seahorn, accept "[QA604 The Bloodsail Buccaneers]" ([G27,77] in STV).
02) Next to you at the top of the Inn, accept "[QA209 Skullsplitter Tusks]" ([G27,77]).
03) Next to you, turn in "[QT1116 Dream Dust in the Swamp]", SKIP "Rumors for Kravel" (for now).
04) Next to you from the dwarf, accept "[QA587 Up to Snuff]".
05) Drop down in the Inn and make BB your new home. Make sure you are repaired/resupplied. You will not come back to town for awhile, so make sure you are well stocked.
06) Next to you, accept "[QA600 Venture Company Mining]" and "[QA621 Zanzil's Secret]".
07) Go next to the bank and accept "[QA617 Akiris by the Bundle]" ([G27,76]).
08) At the Bank next to you put the following items into it: Bundle of Atal'ai Artifacts, Draenethyst Shard, Mire Lord Fungus and 5 Shadow Panther Heart.
09) In the cabin (next to the hanging shark), accept "[QA609 Voodoo Dues]" ([G28,77]).
10) Go north up the docks and from Dizzy One-Eye, accept "[QA576 Keep An Eye Out]" ([G29,76]).
11) Just east of BB along the shore, do "[QC604 The Bloodsail Buccaneers]" along with "[QC587 Up to Snuff]" and "[QC576 Keep An Eye Out]": kill/loot the Bloodsail mobs for the Snuff along with Dizzy's Eye. They can drop from any Bloodsail mob (low drop rates). Also, kill 10 Bloodsail Swashbucklers. And loot the Bloodsail Orders on the small boat ([G28,83]) or it could be on the table at the camp at the end of the beach. And next to you, loot the Bloodsail Charts ([G27,83]) on top of the box next to the eastern most tent.
12) Go west (follow path on map) and do "[QC573 Mok'thardin's Enchantment]" along with "[QC617 Akiris by the Bundle]": kill/loot the Naga Explorers and then work your way up to the top and loot The Holy Spring water fountain over the bridge, ([G29,62]).
13) GROUP 2+ Players: Go north and do the last part of "[QC197 Raptor Mastery]" (Elite): kill/loot Tethis /target (lvl 43 Elite, he has 4 possible spawns, see map). NOTE: If you cannot find a group to do this now, you can try again later at level 47 STV section!
14) Go east across the path to the Ruins of Jubuwal and do "[QC621 Zanzil's Secret]" along with "[QC609 Voodoo Dues]": kill/loot the Zanzil mobs for Zanzil's Mixture and kill/loot the 3 named mobs. Kill/loot Maury "Club Foot" Wilkins /target ([G35,51]). Mobs are tightly packed so be careful. See next step for the other 2 mobs to kill/loot...
15) Kill/loot Jon-Jon the Crow /target ([G35,52]) by the Bonfire.
16) Kill/loot Chucky "Ten Thumbs" /target at the Ruins of Aboraz east ([G40,58], see map on how to get there). Watch out there is numerous stealthed panthers on the pathway there.
17) Go back west to the main path, then north a bit to the ledges (around [G41,43]) and do "[QC600 Venture Company Mining]": kill/loot the Venture Co. mobs (goblins).
18) Go north to the troll Ruins (around [G42,36]) and do "[QC209 Skullsplitter Tusks]" along with "[QC598 Split Bone Necklace]": kill/loot the Skullsplitter trolls. There is more mobs just SE at the other Ruins (around [G47,40]) and NE ([G46,32]).
19) GROUP 2+ Players (or this could be soloable): Go north and do the last part of (if you still need to) "[QC193 Panther Mastery]" (Elite): kill/loot Bhag'thera /target. This lvl 40 elite black panther has 3 different spawn points (see map). If you cannot solo this now, you can try again later at level 47 STV section.
20) Turn in (if you did it) "[QT197 Raptor Mastery]" and "[QT193 Panther Mastery]" (at Nesingwary's Expedition, [G36,11]), then accept (if available) "[QA208 Big Game Hunter]" (Elite). And you can get repaired/resupplied at the camp.
21) Go to Grom'gol (by the Cauldron) and turn in "[QT598 Split Bone Necklace]" ([G32,28]). Next to you, accept "[QA2932 Grim Message]". And click the Bubbling Cauldron to accept "[QA1261 Marg Speaks]".
22) Turn in "[QT573 Mok'thardin's Enchantment]" ([G32,29]). Make sure you are repaired/resupplied. 
23) West at the shore do "[QC628 Excelsior]" (Elite): kill/loot an Elder Saltwater Crocolisks /target (lvl 38 elite). There are 4 possible spawn locations, see map. You should only need to kill/loot one of them. Also these elites spawn by killing the regular Saltwater Crocolisks, so you may need to kill some of them first to get the elites to spawn in.
24) GROUP 2+ Players (or this could be soloable): Go just SE of Grom'gol and do (if you have it) "[QC208 Big Game Hunter]" (Elite): kill/loot King Bangalash /target (lvl 43 Elite at [G38,35]). NOTE: If you cannot solo this now, you can try again later at level 47 STV section!
25) Now could be a good time to see if you have all the pages for "The Green Hills of Stranglethorn". This quest requires that you have the following pages: 1, 4, 6, 8, 10, 11, 14, 16, 18, 20, 21, 24, 25, 26, and 27. You can also find these pages in the AH or from other players. If you have all of them, get them out now and go to Nesingwary's Expedition ([G36,11]) and turn this quest in. If not, you will return to STV one more time in the future for one last chance to find the pages.
26) At Nesingwary's Expedition, turn in (if you did it) "[QT208 Big Game Hunter]" ([G36,11], #2 on map).
27) Hearth to BB.
28) Next to you in the Inn, turn in "[QT600 Venture Company Mining]" and "[QT621 Zanzil's Secret]" ([G27,77]).
29) Go up in the Inn and turn in "[QT209 Skullsplitter Tusks]" and "[QT587 Up to Snuff]". Also accept "[QA1117 Rumors for Kravel]" and "[QA2864 Tran'rek]".
30) Next to you up the steps on the boat-deck, turn in "[QT604 The Bloodsail Buccaneers]", SKIP the next part (for now).
31) Stay up on the top of the docks and go over past the Alliance FP to Tan-Your-Hide Leatherworks and turn in "[QT628 Excelsior]" ([G28,78]).
32) Drop down by the bank and turn in "[QT617 Akiris by the Bundle]" ([G27,76]). Then at the Bank next to you, put into it: Nimboya's Pike and Goblin Rumors.
33) Go in the cabin (next to the hanging shark) and turn in "[QT609 Voodoo Dues]" ([G28,77]). Accept "[QA2872 Stoley's Debt]".
34) Go north up the docks and from Dizzy One-Eye, turn in "[QT576 Keep An Eye Out]" ([G29,76]).
35) Get on the boat at the end of docks ([G26,73]) to go to Ratchet.
36) Once at Ratchet, go to the Flight Master ([G63,37] in The Barrens) and fly to Brackenwall Village, Dustwallow Marsh.
[NX 43-44 Dustwallow Marsh]
]], "Thacen")
